The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, October 24, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Krishnagar, Oct. 23: A 15-year-old girl was allegedly raped last night by the son of a local CPM leader at Nabadwip in Nadia. 

 Police said 18-year-old Sanjib, the son of CPM local committee member Krishnagopal Debnath, raped the girl when she was caught in the rain on her way home and took shelter in a shed in front of his house. Sanjib,who was alone at home, allegedly dragged her inside, an officer said. Around 10 pm, his parents found the girl in their house. Debnath slapped his son and drove her out. The girls father lodged an FIR this morning. Sanjib is absconding.

 Krishnagar: Samit Majumdar, 12, died on Sunday, and 24 were afflicted with enteric diseases at Chapra in Nadia. District chief medical officer Mrinal Kanti Biswas said a medical team has been sent to check if there is any contamination in the drinking water. Six members of a farmers family in the area suffered food poisoning after having biryani at a roadside eatery in Karimpur, 180 km from Calcutta. The condition of a 10-year-old boy was said to be serious. 

 Behrampore: Traffic on National Highway 34 was disrupted for over two hours near Sargachhi in Murshidabad after Bikram Sarkar, 17, was run over by a lorry on Sunday. He was returning home from a market.

 Barasat: Noor Islam Mollah, 30, the alleged kingpin of a drug racket, was arrested at Haroa, about 50 km from Cal- cutta, on Sunday. North 24-Parganas police said he was also involved in several bank dacoities.




